-- Scailex Drops to Lowest in Eight Years After S&P’s Downgrade
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2011-12-18T14:25:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-18/scailex-drops-to-lowest-in-eight-years-after-s-p-s-downgrade.html
Scailex Corp. (SCIX) , an Israeli mobile-
handsets distributor, declined to the lowest in more than eight
years after Standard & Poor’s Maalot lowered the company’s
credit rating to ilBBB+ from ilA-.  The shares retreated 5.8 percent to 16.98 shekels, the
lowest intraday level since October 2003, at 3:58 p.m. in  Tel
Aviv , bringing the decline this year to 78 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
